<tr>
<td style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); padding: 2px 5px 5px;">
<div id="mp-otd">
<p><b><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/October_21" title="October 21">October 21</a></b>: <b><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trafalgar_Day" title="Trafalgar Day">Trafalgar Day</a></b> in various <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Commonwealth_of_Nations" title="Commonwealth of Nations">Commonwealth countries</a></p>
<div style="float: right; margin-left: 0.5em;">
<p><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Florence_Nightingale_headshot.png" class="image" title="Florence Nightingale"><img alt="Florence Nightingale" src="100px-florence_nightingale_headshot.png" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4d/Florence_Nightingale_headshot.png/150px-Florence_Nightingale_headshot.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/4d/Florence_Nightingale_headshot.png 2x" data-file-width="200" data-file-height="200" height="100" width="100"></a></p>
</div>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1805" title="1805">1805</a> – <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Napoleonic_Wars" title="Napoleonic Wars">Napoleonic Wars</a>: <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Horatio_Nelson,_1st_Viscount_Nelson" title="Horatio Nelson, 1st Viscount Nelson">Lord Nelson</a> signalled "<b><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/England_expects_that_every_man_will_do_his_duty" title="England expects that every man will do his duty">England expects that every man will do his duty</a></b>" to the rest of his <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Royal_Navy" title="Royal Navy">Royal Navy</a> forces before they defeated <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pierre-Charles_Villeneuve" title="Pierre-Charles Villeneuve">Pierre-Charles Villeneuve</a> and his combined French–Spanish navy at the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Trafalgar" title="Battle of Trafalgar">Battle of Trafalgar</a> off the coast of Spain's <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cape_Trafalgar" title="Cape Trafalgar">Cape Trafalgar</a>.</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1854" title="1854">1854</a> – <b><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Florence_Nightingale" title="Florence Nightingale">Florence Nightingale</a></b> <i>(pictured)</i> and a staff of 38 nurses were sent to Turkey to help treat wounded British soldiers fighting in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crimean_War" title="Crimean War">Crimean War</a>.</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1910" title="1910">1910</a> – <b><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HMS_Niobe_(1897)" title="HMS Niobe (1897)">HMS&nbsp;<i>Niobe</i></a></b> arrived in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Halifax_Harbour" title="Halifax Harbour">Halifax Harbour</a> to become the first large ship of the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Royal_Canadian_Navy" title="Royal Canadian Navy">Royal Canadian Navy</a>.</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1944" title="1944">1944</a> – <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_War_II" title="World War II">World War II</a>: German forces surrendered to American troops, ending the three-week-long <b><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Aachen" title="Battle of Aachen">Battle of Aachen</a></b>.</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1978" title="1978">1978</a> – After reporting contact with an unidentified aircraft, <b><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disappearance_of_Frederick_Valentich" title="Disappearance of Frederick Valentich">Frederick Valentich</a></b> disappeared in unexplained circumstances while piloting a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cessna_182" title="Cessna 182">Cessna 182L</a> light aircraft over the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bass_Strait" title="Bass Strait">Bass Strait</a> to <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/King_Island_(Tasmania)" title="King Island (Tasmania)">King Island</a>, Australia.</li>
</ul>
<p>More anniversaries: <span class="nowrap"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/October_20" title="October 20">October 20</a> –</span> <span class="nowrap"><b><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/October_21" title="October 21">October 21</a></b> –</span> <span class="nowrap"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/October_22" title="October 22">October 22</a></span></p>
